knowledged the greeting with an absent smile: over her propped-up entwined hands she was following with mocking eyes the receding lady. Van cleared his throat as he gloomily glanced at his half-sister.

“Must be at least thirty-five,” murmured Lucette, “yet still hopes to become his queen.”

